cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.SY, cs.MM

This paper deals with spectrum sharing mechanisms in wireless networks, which falls under the category of networked systems (cs.NI). The paper proposes fair spectrum management algorithms, which involve optimization and allocation of resources, making it relevant to information theory (cs.IT). The paper also addresses regulatory compliance and misbehavior of network operators, which falls under the category of security and privacy (cs.CR). The proposed algorithms involve decision-making and control, which are relevant to systems and control theory (cs.SY). Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of the proposed algorithms using numerical simulations, which falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM).
